Diagnosis.
Body clothed with moderately short and decumbent yellowish setae. Head elongate, 1.3 times as long as wide. Frontoclypeus slightly concave. Prothorax slightly transverse, 0.7 times as long as wide. Elytra 2.0 times as long as wide (EL/EW), surface without raised carinae or tubercles (
Figs 2
, 
59
); epipleura narrow (
Fig. 58
). Aedeagus with parameres longer than penis (
Fig. 90
).
